Lame

Target IP: 10.129.136.147

Scanning


This machine is slow to scan. By scanning it, it shows only four TCP ports are open on the target machine.

Enumeration

Port 21: FTP

After connecting to the FTP application using anonymous login, I did not find anything useful. I did not have write privileges too. However, the target machine is using vsftpd 2.3.4 version application. Doing a Google search shows it is vulnerable, and there is an exploit for it as shown above.

Ports 139 and 445: SMB

I have access to the tmp share which contains interesting files and directories. Using mget *, I downloaded all these files on my machine. But they were not helpful at all.


Doing a Google search for this application version shows it is vulnerable to command execution.

Exploitation & Flags


To exploit the machine, I tried using the FTP exploit first. But that did not work. Then I tried the SMB exploit and it worked! The exploit module I used from Metasploit is multi/samba/usermap_script. The options I set for this exploit are shown above.


After firing the exploit, I gained a root reverse shell connection from the target machine. I investigated further to identify why the FTP exploit did not work. I found out it is due to the firewall. The target machine opens a port on 6200, but incoming request to that port are blocked by the firewall.
